<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="405" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,289,386]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,289,314]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differs from all other subgenera by the combination of eyes naked, preoccipital carina absent laterally, and arolia present on all legs. In females the mandible is four-toothed. This monotypic subgenus is endemic to the Afrotropics.
</paragraph>
